The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                A 25-year-old man was run over by a bus at Padmapukur on Monday afternoon. Bappa Pramanik was crossing CIT Road when the driver of a CTC bus headed towards Baruipur lost control after overtaking a car and knocked him down. Pramanik, a resident of Patharpratima in South 24-Parganas, was hurled on the footpath and sustained injuries on his head, chest and legs. Pedestrians took him to NRS Medical College and Hospital where he succumbed to his injuries. Residents blocked CIT Road to protest the incident. The driver was arrested and the bus impounded.     Sudhansu Panda, a 15-year-old who works as a help at a house in Salt Lakes FE block, has been diagnosed with dengue. He has been admitted to Calcutta Heart Clinic and Hospital. Another blood test will be conducted at the School of Tropical Medicine to confirm the diagnosis.     Bhaskar Sharma, the 24-year-old cop who tried to commit suicide by jumping off the roof of his quarters at Barrackpore Latbagan police training school on Friday, died at RG Kar Hospital on Sunday night.     A Jet Airways flight from Mumbai to Calcutta made a priority landing at Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport on Monday morning after a passenger fell sick on board. D. Basu, 29, complained of severe stomach pain as the aircraft approached Calcutta. A doctor at the airport attended to Basu.    Criminals snatched nearly Rs 1 lakh from a rice trader at Sahebpur in Sonarpur, on the southern fringes, on Sunday night. Police said criminals attacked the trader with sharp weapons as he was cycling to the station.     A man in his mid-50s was seriously injured when a minibus on Ekdalia-BBD Bag route hit him on Gariahat Road on Monday afternoon. Police said the mishap took place around 12.30pm when Sashanka Bakshi was crossing the road. Pedestrians took him to RK Mission Seva Pratisthan, where he was kept under observation. The bus driver fled.    Sankar Roy, 30, was injured after being dashed by a car on CR Avenue around 3.30am on Monday. Driver Bharat Singh lost control of the vehicle and smashed into a road divider. He was arrested and the car impounded. Roy, a resident of Sadananda Aushadhalay Road in Lake Town, was admitted to Medical College and Hospital.    Around 450 teachers of Paschimbanga Ucchyamadhyamik Chuktibhittik Sikshya Samiti started an indefinite agitation in front of Bikash Bhavan in Salt Lake on Monday demanding that they be made permanent employees. According to the associations general secretary Kalyan Sarkar, there are around 1,250 non-permanent contracted teachers working in 700 government-aided schools who are paid a salary of Rs 3,000 and do not get other benefits.    The driver of a trailer was arrested after the vehicle collided with a car on GR Road, under West Port police station, on Sunday evening. The mishap occurred around 5pm when the driver was reversing the trailer.            
